A N A C T
RELATING TO MOTOR AND OTHER VEHICLES -- PUPIL TRANSPORTATION
VEHICLES
Introduced By: Senators Ujifusa, Murray, de la Cruz, DiPalma, Mack, McKenney, Gallo,
Zurier, LaMountain, and DiMario
Date Introduced: March 07, 2025
Referred To: Senate Education
(Dept. of Education)
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 31-22.1-1 of the General Laws in Chapter 31-22.1 entitled "Pupil
2 Transportation Vehicles" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 31-22.1-1. Pupil transportation vehicle — Definition.
4 A pupil transportation vehicle is a motor vehicle designed and constructed to seat not more
5 than eight (8) ten (10) passengers including plus the operator, used by a school committee to
6 provide the transportation services required by law or regulation to students being conveyed along
7 a fixed school transportation route. In particular, such vehicles may be used to provide the
8 transportation services required by § 16-21-1, § 16-21.1-1, et seq., and § 16-24-4 on routes in which
9 only small numbers of students are being conveyed.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
